Sakamakonmu ya nuna cewa adadin shari'o'in COVID-19 da aka bayar da rahoton sun karu cikin sauri a cikin ƙasashen EU/Yankin Tattalin Arzikin Turai da Burtaniya.
Abubuwan da aka lura a cikin abubuwan da suka faru na COVID-19 sun nuna cewa annobar tana ci gaba da haɓaka cikin ƙididdiga a cikin dukkan ƙasashe.
Wannan ya bambanta da yadda ƙasashe ke cikin matakai daban-daban, canza amsar lafiyar jama'a da kuma ma'anar shari'o'i daban-daban a cikin ƙasashe da kuma ayyuka daban-daban don zaɓar marasa lafiya don tabbatar da COVID-19, gami da gwajin gwaji.
A farkon watan Maris na shekarar 2020, likitoci a yankin da kasar Italiya ta sha wahala sosai sun ruwaito halin da ake ciki a yankin cewa kashi 10% na marasa lafiya na COVID-19 suna bukatar kulawa mai kyau, kuma wasu kafofin sun ruwaito cewa asibitoci da kuma cibiyoyin gaggawa a yankunan suna aiki da iyakar iyawarsu.
Bayanai game da karɓar COVID-19 a asibitoci da/ko cibiyoyin kula da marasa lafiya a halin yanzu suna samuwa a matakin EU/Yankin Tattalin Arzikin Turai don kashi 6% da 1% na shari'o'in, kowanne (ba a bayyana bayanan ba).
